This paper deals with the security threat of backdoor contamination in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of statistical analysis and EM algorithm, which are common techniques in cryptography and security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper deals with the robustness of the proposed technique, which is a common concern in neural networks (cs.NE).
